I made a really annoying strobe light by setting using a formula like this in an update loop

```
        float h = c.Hue();
        h += timestep * .01;
        if (h > .99)
            h -= .99;
        c.FromHSL(h, 1.0, .5, 1.0);
```

when the value approaches .333 / .666 / .999 it resets around .03 backwards and won't analogously travel over said limits.

also setting the h to .333 is green while .3334 is noticabbly blue

The function def is: 

```
engine->RegisterObjectMethod("XMLElement", "bool SetVariantVector(Array<Variant>@+)", asFUNCTION(XMLElementSetVariantVector), asCALL_CDECL_OBJLAST);
```

But the static method for conversion doesn't return anything it should be:

```
static bool XMLElementSetVariantVector(CScriptArray* value, XMLElement* ptr)
{
    VariantVector src;
    ArrayToVariantVector(value, src);
    return ptr->SetVariantVector(src);
}
```

Thought it might be simpler to fix directly instead of branch and pull requesting.
